<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="768" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.001M18/49: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-10T15:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>160. President Machado informed the members of his Cabinet that he wanted
                            them to confer and advise him whether in the best interests of Cuba he
                            should resign the Presidency.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>